 describing the\nindecomposable modules. Finally, we give a new generalization of\nK\\\"othe-Cohen-Kaplansky theorem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jun 2022 20:19:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Jun 2022 22:42:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 19 Jul 2022 00:54:39 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 24 Jul 2022 22:18:07 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 09:48:22 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 28 Dec 2022 10:45:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-29"}
